# {{INSTANCE_NAME}} file search

Route file-finding to a remote **plocate** trigram-index server. Searches are
sub-millisecond even on trees with millions of files, and a process restart
never rescans — the index lives on disk.

## When to use me

- Locating a file **inside {{SCOPE}}** by (partial) name or path.
- Glob patterns: `*.rs`, `**/2024/*.log`, `src/**/*.ts`.
- Any time `glob`/`grep` would otherwise walk a large tree — prefer the index.

## When NOT to use me

- Searching inside a single small project you are already in; local `glob` is
  faster and sees uncommitted files.
- Searching file **contents** — this index stores paths only.
- Anywhere outside {{SCOPE}} — that path is not indexed here.

## How to call me

Call MCP tool `search_files` (substring, or glob when the query contains
`*` `?` `[`) or `glob` (explicit glob) on {{INSTANCE_URL}}.
Results are **relative paths**, one per line, capped by the server's
`--max-results`.

{{NOTES}}

## Prerequisite

The MCP server must be registered with the agent. opencode:

    opencode mcp add {{INSTANCE_NAME}} --url {{INSTANCE_URL}}

Claude Code:

    claude mcp add --transport http {{INSTANCE_NAME}} {{INSTANCE_URL}}
